 Arikel, I believe that if you look at the current research of Social Psychology you may find that human intuition/reason is not as pronounced as you maintain. Sterotypes are everywhere...... we use them everyday in everyway. <br>
<br>
 Arikel said &quot;If we let sterotypes rule our thinking...our society would be less advanced as it is&quot;<br>
<br>
 Response: How can you maintain you know how people think, and use sterotypes, when you have done/ read little or no research on sterotypes? Your viewpoint must be based predominantly on intuition. Sterotypes may not rule our thinking as you say Arikel, but on some level they serve a purpose. Sterotypes are deeply ingrained in our minds. The concept of belief preservence which I eluded to earlier is defined as such:<br>
<br>
Belief preservance: Persistence of one's initial conception, as when the basis for one's belief is discredited but an explaination of why the belief might be true survives. <br>
<br>
 For example once we consider, why an accused person might be guilty, why an offending stranger acts a certain way, or why a favored stock might rise in value, our explainations might SURVIVE challenging evidence to the CONTRARY. (Davies, 1997; Jelalian &amp; Miller,1984). Keep in mind, one or two studies on a subject is not the defining word, but it beats intuition. <br>
<br>
 Arikel, in your first post you made a rather large sterotype of the poster, that he was dumb, uneducated, and not serious about the issue based on one post. You further went on to sterotype liberals as smarted, better educated, and more serious about &quot;real world&quot; issues then &quot;far Wing Reagan conservative&quot;, whatever the hell that is. <br>
<br>
 You are correct that my sterotypes about liberals have NO substancial real world basis to them. I think however that you are too hard on the Ronald Reagan's of the world,  they have their place, and that's why I proceeded to slam you liberals around abit<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
 In conclusion, I don't agree with the Al Gore's(far left), or the Rush Limbaugh's (Far right) of the world, however I do think they both have their purpose. As long as The USA has a ballance of the two I think we will be fine. Lastly, I think you just don't want to talk to me because I don't agree with you. -Mec<br>
